CHANGELOG.md:672:- Added depth-2 wizard end-to-end test coverage (frac-0121): `tests/test_wizard.py` now declares `depth: 2` in its module docstring and includes `WizardEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `promptclaw/wizard.py` startup wizard surface through one realistic lifecycle: `init_project(...)` scaffolds a fresh temp project; `run_startup_wizard(...)` walks the base questionnaire (project pitch, task families, success outputs), defaults the agent roster to `["codex", "claude", "gemini"]`, queues per-agent strength questions, captures routing/verification/autonomy/ambiguity/boundaries answers, and triggers the `permission_boundaries` follow-up via the `"fully autonomous"` autonomy answer; the resulting project has every expected artifact (`prompts/00-project-vision.md`, `prompts/01-agent-roles.md`, `prompts/02-routing-rules.md`, `prompts/agents/{codex,claude,gemini}.md`, `docs/STARTUP_PROFILE.md`, `docs/STARTUP_TRANSCRIPT.md`, `.promptclaw/onboarding/startup-session.md`, and `promptclaw.json`); the persisted vision contains the project pitch and approval-gate text; `load_config(...)` exposes the project description, `routing.verification_enabled=True`, `routing.ask_user_on_ambiguity=True`, the three default agents enabled with their `instruction_file` set to `prompts/agents/<slug>.md` and capabilities of `["coding", "implementation", "testing"]` / `["architecture", "specification", "verification"]` / `["docs", "synthesis", "writing"]`; the focused helpers agree with the lifecycle (`parse_agent_roster("")` returns the default roster, `looks_vague("anything")` is `True`, `mentions_any(...)` returns `True`/`False` symmetrically, `infer_capabilities(DEFAULT_AGENT_STRENGTHS["codex"], "codex")` returns `["coding", "implementation", "refactoring", "testing"]`, `lead_lane_text("coding, implementation")` returns `"code-heavy execution and implementation"`, `verification_fit_text("verification, analysis")` returns `"strong verifier candidate"`, and `sentence_or_list(...)` produces a single line for one item and a `- `-prefixed bulleted list for multiple items); the captured `output_func` blocks include the `"Startup Wizard"` banner and the `"Ready"` summary card; and a primitive diagnostic of the roster, applied config description and routing flags, per-agent capabilities and instruction files, the relative-path file list, and a focused-helper map round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_wizard_depth.py` pins the base test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method plus a machine-readable depth marker. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because `promptclaw/wizard.py` already produced the required lifecycle output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4685 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:708:- Added depth-2 render-replay end-to-end test coverage (frac-0105): `tests/test_render_replay.py` now includes `RenderReplayEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/replay.py` public surface through one mapping-score → sidecar-delta → performed-part → audio-export → persisted-delta replay lifecycle. The coverage verifies score-event dictionaries are coerced into rendered `Event` objects, score-level fields remain owned by the original score even when deltas repeat `pitch`/`role`/`nominal_beat`, performance fields and sensor deltas are overlaid, `seed_path` values replay as tuples, duplicate rule-stack entries collapse into ordered unique `applied_rules`, seed metadata is preserved as strings, diagnostics round-trip through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`, `export_audio(...)` persists the default `.delta.json` track and readable sidecar, and replaying from the persisted delta path reproduces the original event-sequence hash. `tests/test_test_render_replay_depth.py` pins the render-replay test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the replay module already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4635 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:710:- Added depth-2 render-events end-to-end test coverage (frac-0104): `tests/test_render_events.py` now includes `RenderEventsEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `src/cypherclaw/render/events.py` public surface through one realistic two-event lifecycle: a non-trivial `SectionEnvelope` is sampled and per-parameter `value_at(...)` agrees with the `SectionEnvelopeSample` for every `SECTION_ENVELOPE_PARAMETERS` channel, a custom `PerformanceIntent` round-trips its declared fields, two `Event` instances (phrase-start `IntentTag.BUILD` and phrase-end / cadential `IntentTag.SETTLE`) populate the full `Event` field surface, `lock_score_fields()` freezes every member of `Event.SCORE_LEVEL_FIELDS` while leaving sensor / timing / `rule_stack` mutable, both events round-trip through `to_json_dict()`/`from_json_dict()`, `to_json()`/`from_json()`, and `to_osc_bundle()`/`from_osc_bundle()` with structural equality and preserved `seed_path` tuples, and a combined diagnostic of `IntentTag` membership, `VALID_ARC_SHAPES`, `SECTION_ENVELOPE_PARAMETERS`, the sampled envelope values, the `PerformanceIntent` snapshot, and both event JSON dicts round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_render_events_depth.py` pins the render-events test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the events module already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4631 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:714:- Recorded render-ablation depth-2 completion (frac-0102d): re-ran the full validation gate (`pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/`) on top of the merged frac-0102/0102a/0102b/0102c work and confirmed `4620 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean with no failures introduced by the new render-ablation assertions. Appended a `Depth-2 Completion` section to `sdp/notes/frac-0102a-render-ablation-depth.md` that names the locked `RenderAblationEndToEndTests` class and `test_full_pipeline_final_rendered_artifact_shape_and_content` method, cross-references the public surface (`rule_identifiers`, `filter_active_rules`, `ablate`, `build_ablation_cases`, `run_ablation_suite`, `summarize_ablation_suite`) in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/ablation.py`, marks each previously open gap as closed with the delivering task ID (`frac-0102` and `frac-0102c`), and lists the duplicate active/disabled IDs and no-rule default-renderer path as intentionally still open. Added `tests/test_frac_0102d_depth_completion.py` as a contract test pinning the new section's required fragments and at least four `- Closed:` bullets. The pre-existing `tests/test_frac_0102a_notes.py` baseline contract continues to pass unchanged. No production code, dependencies, migrations, provider secrets, database columns, runtime state directories, HTTP routes, or auth behavior were introduced; startup identity hardening anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:716:- Added depth-2 render-ablation final-artifact assertion coverage (frac-0102c): `tests/test_test_render_ablation_depth.py` now requires `RenderAblationEndToEndTests.test_full_pipeline_final_rendered_artifact_shape_and_content`, and `tests/test_render_ablation.py` drives the full ablation pipeline through `rule_identifiers(...)`, `filter_active_rules(...)`, `ablate(...)`, `build_ablation_cases(...)`, `run_ablation_suite(...)`, and `summarize_ablation_suite(...)` using a deterministic structured renderer. The final suite result disables `phrase_arch` and `microtiming`, leaves only `metric_accent` active, and asserts the complete rendered artifact shape/content (`schema_version`, `score_id`, `seed_signature`, `active_rule_ids`, `sections`, `events`, and `metadata`) plus JSON round-trip behavior. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the ablation API already preserves renderer output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4620 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:718:- Added depth-2 primary render-path end-to-end test coverage (frac-0102b): `tests/test_render_pass.py` now includes `RenderPassEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/pass_.py` public surface through one register → enable → quantity → gate → apply lifecycle: a three-rule stack registered out of canonical order (`R3`, `R1`, `R2`) with `R1` quantity-disabled, `R2` carrying `quantities={"R2": 0.5}`, and `R3` role-gated by `frozenset({"melody", "bass"})` canonicalizes to `("R1", "R2", "R3")` with `effective_k` returning `0.0`/`0.5`/`1.0`; the first `apply(...)` returns a `PerformedPart` whose `applied_rules` skip the disabled `R1`, whose `quantities` record all three effective `k` values, and whose score-tree trace carries structurally correct `rule_id`/`k`/`roles` entries for `R2` (no role gate) and `R3` (forwarded role-gate frozenset); the second `apply(...)` with `quantity_overrides={"R1": 0.75}` re-enables `R1` so `applied_rules == ("R1", "R2", "R3")` in canonical order with the override `k=0.75` reflected in both `quantities` and the trace; and a combined diagnostic of rule order, effective-k map, and both performed-part snapshots (with `frozenset` role gates explicitly converted to sorted lists) round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_render_pass_depth.py` pins the render-pass test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the module already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4619 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:722:- Added depth-2 render-ablation end-to-end test coverage (frac-0102): `tests/test_render_ablation.py` now includes `RenderAblationEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/ablation.py` public surface through one baseline → plan → suite → summary lifecycle: `rule_identifiers(...)` and `filter_active_rules(...)` resolve a three-rule active stack and a single-rule disable, `ablate(...)` reruns the injected renderer with `phrase_arch` removed, `build_ablation_cases(...)` produces both default single-rule and explicit pair plans, `run_ablation_suite(...)` records the full-stack baseline plus per-case rendered events, `changed` flags, `remaining_rule_ids`, and operator-readable summaries, and `summarize_ablation_suite(...)` aggregates the JSON-safe rule-id, case-count, changed/unchanged-count, and per-case summary fields, all round-tripped through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_render_ablation_depth.py` pins the render-ablation test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the module already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4612 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
