CHANGELOG.md:788:- Added depth-2 counterpoint_rules end-to-end test coverage (frac-0069): `tests/test_counterpoint_rules.py` now ships a `CounterpointRulesEndToEndTests` class that drives the existing public counterpoint registry surface (`best_rule_for_phase`, `rules_for_phase`, `rules_for_leader_role`, `rules_for_follower_role`, `rules_for_voice_pair`, `resolve_rule`, `get_rule`, `motion_profile`, `analyze_dissonance`, `verify_resolution_sequence`, `resolution_completeness_score`, `weighted_voice_leading_smoothness`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, `counterpoint_pair_summary`) end-to-end through 11 scenario tests covering: per-phase best-rule resolution against the documented Divination/Emergence/Conversation/Convergence/Crystallization expectations with affinity bounded in [0, 1]; voice-pair query intersections and unknown-role empty-result handling; `resolve_rule` known/alias/unknown fallback chains plus registry fallback validity; mixed-sequence motion classification including single-note and mismatched-length safe defaults; contrary-motion `score_counterpoint_fit` / `rank_counterpoint_rules` agreement with `recommend_counterpoint_rule` and bounded sub-metrics; realistic melody/bass dissonance + resolution analysis with JSON-safe annotation payloads; `counterpoint_pair_summary` payload shape, key set, JSON round-trip, and consistency with the underlying `CounterpointFit`; registry coverage equality with `REQUIRED_RELATIONSHIPS` and `REQUIRED_PHASES`; mixed-dissonance resolution completeness and weighted-smoothness penalties; voice-pair-compatible-only ranking for melody/bass pairs; phase-sensitive summary differences with JSON round-trip; and parallel/static/oblique extreme motion-profile sequences. `tests/test_test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins `tests/test_counterpoint_rules.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing `TestRegistryCompleteness`, `TestEntryFields`, `TestArcPhaseAffinity`, `TestVoicePairQueries`, `TestLookups`, `TestIntervalConstraints`, `TestImmutability`, `TestVerificationAndScoring`, and `TestDissonanceMetadata` assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4476 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:792:- Added depth-2 constitution end-to-end test coverage (frac-0067): `tests/test_constitution.py` now ships a `ConstitutionEndToEndTests` class that drives the existing public `Constitution` API end-to-end through 30 scenario tests covering JSON rule loading and field mapping, missing/None path fallback, malformed-JSON tolerance, unknown-extension JSON fallback, regex matching, keyword matching with case-insensitive substring comparison, combined pattern + keyword rules where either path matches, phase and agent filtering (active and inactive), compound phase + agent gating, phase-agnostic rule fan-out across every phase argument, message-vs-description fallback, `hard_rules` / `soft_rules` / `rules_for_phase` filtering, and the full evaluate → `should_block` pipeline under each `EnforcementMode` (MONITOR, SOFT, FULL) including empty-violation no-block in every mode and multi-rule violations carrying the right `rule_id`, severity, and message. `tests/test_test_constitution_depth.py` pins `tests/test_constitution.py` at fractal depth >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`) and requires the end-to-end class. Existing `TestConstitutionLoading`, `TestConstitutionEvaluate`, `TestConstitutionHelpers`, and `TestShouldBlock` assertions and the production `promptclaw/coherence/constitution.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4458 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:796:- Added depth-2 coherence-engine end-to-end test coverage (frac-0065): `tests/test_coherence_engine.py` now ships a new `TestCoherenceEngineEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public `CoherenceEngine` and `NullCoherenceEngine` surface through complete end-to-end paths. The new tests walk every hook in canonical order (`pre_routing → post_routing → pre_lead → post_lead → pre_verify → post_verify → finalize`) and verify event types, phases, monotonic sequence numbers, run-id propagation, and SQLite persistence across an engine rebuild; write a `constitution.json` with one HARD and one SOFT keyword rule and confirm `EnforcementMode.FULL` blocks `post_routing`/`post_lead`/`post_verify` while `EnforcementMode.MONITOR` records the same violations without blocking, propagating HARD severity, both rule ids, and a negative trust delta on `post_lead`; record two architectural decisions through `record_decision` and confirm `pre_routing`/`pre_lead`/`pre_verify` inject the `## Active Decisions` block with at least one matching title; step the graduation manager across three `finalize` calls plus alternating `record_graduation_observation` outcomes and verify the run/observation/true-/false-positive counters and stable enforcement mode; round-trip a full replayed event payload through `json.dumps` with sorted keys and verify each event's `sequence_number`, `run_id`, and dict `payload`; and loop `NullCoherenceEngine` across multiple run ids confirming every hook returns an approved verdict with empty violations and empty injected context plus an empty replay. `tests/test_test_coherence_engine_depth.py` pins `tests/test_coherence_engine.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing `TestCoherenceEngine` and `TestNullCoherenceEngine` assertions and the production `promptclaw/coherence/engine.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4421 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:816:- Added depth-2 end-to-end accompaniment test coverage (frac-0055): `tests/test_accompaniment.py` now ships a new `TestAccompanimentEndToEnd` class that drives the existing Korsakov accompaniment public surface (`DensityTracker`, `select_accompaniment_type`, `breathing_swell`, `should_transition_gradually`, `should_pedal`, `pedal_note`, `get_pattern`, and the six pattern generators) through end-to-end multi-step pytest methods. The new tests sweep the documented density bands and verify the inverse-density rule, iterate every pattern type 1-6 to assert non-empty events with positive amps/releases, sweep `breathing_swell` over rest/active/edge inputs, walk full phrase boundaries through `should_pedal` + `pedal_note`, run the dense-melody and resting-melody pipelines end-to-end through a synthetic `DensityTracker` window, and pin a six-bar composer loop. A `test_test_accompaniment_reaches_depth_two` gate test asserts the file's fractal classification is at least depth 2. Existing `TestDensityTracker`, `TestSelectAccompanimentType`, `TestPatterns`, `TestPedalPoint`, `TestBreathing`, and `TestTransition` assertions are preserved unchanged; `tests/test_accompaniment_depth.py`, `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py`, and the startup identity anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:856:- Added depth-2 startle daemon processing (frac-0034): `my-claw/tools/startle_daemon.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `read_room_activity`, `amp_from_room`, `update_baseline`, `baseline_value`, `render_output`, `write_output`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus a `DaemonState` dataclass that combines the existing `senseweave.startle.StartleState` with a rolling-baseline tracker. The daemon now reads `/tmp/room_activity.json`, takes the louder of `window_mic_amp` / `cypherclaw_mic_amp`, maintains a 20-sample rolling-median baseline (with a non-zero floor so the detector never sees a degenerate baseline), runs the existing `update_startle` rules, and atomically writes the consumer contract (`startled`, `startle_count`, `cooldown_active`, `face_reaction`, `should_mute`, `amp`, `baseline`, `timestamp`) consumed by `inner_life.world_model.poll_state`. Loop control gains `--once`, `--interval`, `--room-path`, `--state-path`, and `--max-iterations`; existing `senseweave.startle` rules are unchanged. `tests/test_startle_daemon.py` pins import safety, baseline/amp helpers, end-to-end loud-room startle output, and quiet-room loop output; `tests/test_startle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:874:- Added depth-2 motif-lifecycle report helpers (frac-0025): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/motif_lifecycle.py` now exposes frozen `MotifLifecycleStep` and `MotifLifecycleReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lifecycle_state_index`, `build_lifecycle_step`, `canonical_lifecycle_path`, `build_lifecycle_report`, and `summarize_lifecycle_report` so composer/diagnostics callers can advance a motif through the one canonical lifecycle path and emit a JSON-safe operator summary with ordered history, current/terminal state, valid next states, canonical state counts, contour/rhythm/material deltas, and per-step state-band/material diagnostics. Existing transition rules, deterministic transformations, `advance(...)`, `MotifLifecycleManager`, and repertoire-shape recall behavior are preserved; `tests/test_motif_lifecycle_depth.py` pins the new report surface, manager end-to-end agreement, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_motif_lifecycle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:880:- Added depth-2 sample-lab report helpers (frac-0022): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sample_lab.py` now exposes a frozen `SamplePlanReport` dataclass plus pure helpers `density_band`, `threshold_band`, `intensity_band`, `build_sample_plan_report`, and `summarize_sample_plan_report` so EMSD operator/diagnostics callers can resolve a `SamplePlan` together with its `sample_bank` freshness and fallback rule into one operator-readable view (source identity and capture path, refresh and freshness seconds, fallback list, cadence state, section function, transforms tuple plus count, density and named density band, buffer seconds, trigger threshold and named threshold band, intensity and named intensity band, and study focus) and emit a stable JSON-safe summary. Existing `SAMPLE_SOURCES`, `SAMPLE_SOURCE_ALIASES`, `SAMPLE_FALLBACKS`, `canonical_sample_source_name`, `sample_source`, `sample_bank`, and `plan_environmental_sampling` semantics are preserved (cadence and section-function shaping unchanged); `SamplePlan` now also carries the resolved `cadence_state` so reports can be built without re-passing it. `tests/test_sample_lab_depth.py` pins the band cutpoints, plan/bank field mirroring, alias-to-canonical bank resolution, section-function carry-through, JSON-safe summary shape, end-to-end downstream use, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_sample_lab.py`, `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence`, and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:884:- Added depth-2 silence budget report helpers (frac-0020): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/silence_budget.py` now exposes frozen `LaneSilenceBudgetStat` and `SilenceBudgetReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_silence_budget_stat`, `analyze_silence_budget`, and `summarize_silence_budget_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R10 rule once and inspect per-lane phrase outcomes (lane name, role, rendered step count, original phrase count, breath-extension count, tacet step count, distinct tacet phrase count, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `DEFAULT_TARGET_DENSITY`, `DEFAULT_THRESHOLD`, `SilenceBudgetRule.apply`, and `apply_silence_budget` semantics are preserved so render-pipeline callers and `tests/test_silence_budget_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_silence_budget_depth.py` pins tacet-trigger lane shaping, breath-extension lane shaping, non-melodic non-application, scene/song/pattern aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain startup identity regression anchors.
