sdp/verification/t-037@20260416t181925z-verify.md:15:`replay(score, seeds, delta_track)` is implemented and returns a `PerformedPart`. Score-level fields are owned by the input score; only performance-level fields (velocity, timing, articulation, seed_path, rule_stack, sensor_* fields) are overlaid from the delta track. Matching is by `event_id` (preferred) then by sequence index — correct fallback logic. `Event.mark_rendered()` is called per event. `seeds` is stored in `PerformedPart.metadata`. All API surfaces (`SCORE_LEVEL_FIELDS`, `mark_rendered`, `from_json_dict`, `to_json_dict`) verified to exist in `src/cypherclaw/render/events.py`.
sdp/verification/t-037@20260416t181925z-verify.md:27:`DeltaTrack` type accepts file paths, raw sequences, and sidecar-style mappings — good defensive input handling. `_apply_delta` correctly skips score-level fields and handles `metadata`, `seed_path`, and `rule_stack` as special cases requiring type coercion.
