sdp/verification/t-018@20260416t054258za-verify.md:11:{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-04-16T20:11:17.602Z","role":"user","content":"# Verification: Task T-018@20260416T054258Za\n\n**Task:** Create counterpoint_rules.py registry with 6 relationship types (contrary, oblique, parallel, echo, commentary, completion), each as a frozen dataclass with voice-pair constraints, interval rules, and arc-phase affinity. Include lookup/selection functions following the strategy registry pattern.\n**Tier:** T1\n\nYou are the VERIFY agent for this task. The LEAD agent has completed their work.\n\n\n## Review Checklist\n\n1. **Review recent commits:**\n   ```bash\n   git log --oneline -5\n   git diff HEAD~3 --stat\n   ```\n\n2. **Review code changes:**\n   ```bash\n   git diff HEAD~3\n   ```\n\n4. **Check ESCALATIONS.md** for any flagged issues.\n\n5. **Run the test suite:**\n   ```bash\n   pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x\n   ```\n\n## Evaluation Criteria\n\nEvaluate the work against these five dimensions:\n\n1. **Correctness**: Does the output match the requirements/spec?\n2. **Completeness**: Are there gaps, missing edge cases, or unhandled scenarios?\n3. **Consistency**: Does the output follow established patterns and conventions?\n4. **Security**: Are there vulnerabilities, leaked secrets, or unsafe practices?\n5. **Quality**: Does the output meet the quality gates for this phase?\n\n## Output\n\nWrite your verification report and all findings to this exact path:\n`sdp/verification/t-018@20260416t054258za-verify.md`\nDo not use a different filename or directory.\n\nUse this format:\n\n```markdown\n# Verification Report — T-018@20260416T054258Za\n\n**Verify Agent:** [your agent name]\n**Date:** [today]\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** [list files reviewed]\n\n## Correctness\n[assessment]\n\n## Completeness\n[assessment]\n\n## Consistency\n[assessment]\n\n## Security\n[assessment]\n\n## Quality\n[assessment]\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] [Issue — severity: blocking/minor]\n\n## Verdict: [PASS | PASS WITH NOTES | FAIL]\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\n[specific items to address]\n```\n\nCommit the verification report.\n\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\n\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: [x] **Issue — severity: blocking**: New self-critique logic is not wired into the active composition pipeline. `my-claw/tools/senseweave/tracker_compiler.py` and `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py` continue to call `score_from_mood(...)` directly in piece generation; `revise_score(...)` from `senseweave.self_critique` is never imported or used by composition/playback flow..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Integrate the new `revise_score(...)` path into score generation before tracker/build or playback handoff (both gate-backed and fallback paths)..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that verifies a piece goes through critique/revision before being finalized for playback, with assertions that failed metrics can trigger one bounded rewrite attempt and that the final score is selected from the two-pass result..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Incomplete budget enforcement: budget fields for grain density, global density multiplier, LLM suppression, and DSP budget are computed but never applied in `tracker_solo_song`, so sample/grain and primary-form fallback is not actually enforced (`my-claw/tools/senseweave/resource_governor.py`, `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py`). Severity: blocking..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Startup hardening gap: `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py` does not call `bootstrap_identity()` before startup announcement and main loop, while this path is still part of the runnable daemon entry points (`my-claw/docs/PROJECT_GUIDE.md` and system scripts/tests reference it), so first-boot identity creation is not guaranteed in that mode. Severity: blocking..\n"}
