ent]\n\n## Completeness\n[assessment]\n\n## Consistency\n[assessment]\n\n## Security\n[assessment]\n\n## Quality\n[assessment]\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] [Issue — severity: blocking/minor]\n\n## Verdict: [PASS | PASS WITH NOTES | FAIL]\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\n[specific items to address]\n```\n\nCommit the verification report.\n\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\n\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Ensure this path is used on both standalone and federated modes..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that exercises startup and verifies identity persistence between boots..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Re-run pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x after wiring the startup path..\n"}
