/Users/anthony/Programming/sdp-cli/prd-sdp-wrapper-verification-guardrails.md:16:| SI-002 | Verifier rule (refined to avoid false-positives on layered test suites): if a task's spec contains an `## Engine Surface Snapshot` section AND zero tests in the change-set exercise any symbol from that snapshot via a real call (i.e., not behind `Mock()` / `MagicMock()` / `patch(...)` against the snapshot name), the verdict downgrades from PASS to PASS WITH NOTES with a `notes` block citing the gap. If tests both mock AND call the real symbol elsewhere, no downgrade. | MUST | T1 | A test file with only `mock_engine = Mock(spec=NarrativeMemory); ...` patterns against snapshot names triggers PASS WITH NOTES; a sibling test file that imports `NarrativeMemory` and calls it directly removes the downgrade. |
/Users/anthony/Programming/sdp-cli/prd-sdp-wrapper-verification-guardrails.md:17:| SI-003 | Verifier rule for migration tasks: any task whose spec mentions `ALTER TABLE`, `CREATE TABLE`, `migration`, or `schema change` cannot reach PASS until its verification report includes evidence of running the migration against a real database — minimally a `PRAGMA table_info(<table>)` snapshot (SQLite) or `\d <table>` snapshot (Postgres) after the migration with the new column visible. | MUST | T1 | T-007 in the original narrative-api plan would have failed verification under this rule until someone ran the SQL and pasted the post-migration schema; passes once that evidence is present. |
