/Users/anthony/Programming/sdp-cli/sdp/verification/t-003@20260405t223932z-verify.md:83:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-06T00:33:15.169Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1775435595169_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-003 @specs/t-003@20260405t223932z-spec.md\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-06\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `src/sdp/state/_db_impl.py`\n- `src/sdp/state/models.py`\n- `src/sdp/fractal.py`\n- `src/sdp/_cli_impl.py`\n- `tests/test_fractal_depth_history.py`\n- `tests/test_fractal.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation correctly adds the `fractal_depth_history` table and index to the SDP state database. Each `fractal scan` persists results using batch insertion. The `fractal history` command and underlying database query methods correctly filter results by module path and timestamp. Manual verification confirmed that running `sdp-cli fractal scan` populates the database and `sdp-cli fractal history` displays the recorded snapshots.\n\n## Completeness\nAll requirements from the specification and PRD (FRAC-003) are met:\n- `fractal_depth_history` table exists with correct schema.\n- `fractal scan` persists results to DB by default.\n- Repeated scans create timestamped rows.\n- Trend queries are enabled via `query_fractal_depth_changes` (tested in unit tests).\n- `fractal history` CLI subcommand is implemented and functional.\n- Modules with `depth=-1` are correctly excluded from persistence.\n\n## Consistency\nThe implementation follows established patterns:\n- Database migrations use the idempotent `_ensure_X_table()` pattern called from `migrate()`.\n- CLI commands use `typer` and are integrated into the existing `fractal` app group.\n- Dataclasses are defined in `models.py`.\n- Tests use `pytest` and `hypothesis` for property-based testing, consistent with other high-quality parts of the codebase.\n\n## Security\nNo security issues found. Database interactions use parameterized queries (via `?` placeholders) to prevent SQL injection. No sensitive information is logged or stored.\n\n## Quality\nThe code quality is high:\n- Efficient batch inserts using `executemany`.\n- Clear separation of concerns between DB implementation, data models, and CLI logic.\n- Comprehensive test suite with 27 new tests covering schema, migrations, queries, and CLI integration.\n- Property-based tests ensure robustness for arbitrary module lists.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid and well-tested. No further actions required.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-003 @20260405t223932z-verify.md"}}
