/Users/anthony/Programming/sdp-cli/sdp/verification/t-001@20260512t162342z-verify.md:20:Hook placement is correct. `_record_task_run_fitness_events()` is called immediately after `update_task_run()` commits the verdict successfully, gated by `task_run_persisted = True`. The hook writes exactly two events per natural task run: one for the lead agent (role=`"lead"`) and one for the verify agent (role=`"verify"`), both carrying the same `summary_verdict` that was written to the state DB. The `verdict_to_quality` mapping covers all six documented verdicts (PASS → 1.0, PASS WITH NOTES → 0.7, NEEDS_REVIEW → 0.4, TIMEOUT → 0.0, FAIL → 0.0, ESCALATED → -0.2). The `summary_verdict` and `completed_at` values used by the hook are set before the `update_task_run` call, so the fitness DB records the same verdict as the state DB.
