# Agent Development Protocol (ADP)

The full ADP v4.0 specification is maintained at:

**[docs/agent-development-protocol.md](docs/agent-development-protocol.md)**

The ADP governs how agents write code within the SDP pipeline. Key concepts:

- **Task Tiers:** T1 (Light), T2 (Standard), T3 (Full)
- **Phases:** Explore → Specify → Test → Implement → Verify → Document
- **Test Locking:** Tests written before implementation are locked
- **Quality Gates:** Automated checks at each phase boundary
- **Dual-Agent Verification:** A different agent reviews work at every gate

